y individual channels configured by associated binding elements, for example, Text Message Encoding, Security, Reliable Messaging, and Transactions.","pos":[3740,3946]},{"content":"Each channel recognizes headers from the associated namespace and marks them as understood.","pos":[3947,4038]},{"content":"Once a message enters the dispatcher, the operation formatter reads headers expected by the corresponding message/operation contract and marks them understood.","pos":[4039,4198]},{"content":"Then the dispatcher verifies whether any remaining headers are not understood but marked as <ph id=\"ph1\">`mustUnderstand`</ph> and throws an exception.","pos":[4199,4332],"source":" Then the dispatcher verifies whether any remaining headers are not understood but marked as `mustUnderstand` and throws an exception."},{"content":"Messages that contain <ph id=\"ph1\">`mustUnderstand`</ph> headers that are targeted at the recipient are not processed by recipient application code.","pos":[4333,4463],"source":" Messages that contain `mustUnderstand` headers that are targeted at the recipient are not processed by recipient application code."},{"content":"Such layered processing allows for separation between infrastructure layers and application layers of the SOAP node:","pos":[4465,4581]},{"content":"B1111: Headers that are not understood are detected after the message is processed by the WCF infrastructure channel stack, but before it is processed by application","pos":[4585,4750]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">`mustUnderstand`</ph> header value differs between SOAP 1.1 and SOAP 1.2.","pos":[4757,4829],"source":"The `mustUnderstand` header value differs between SOAP 1.1 and SOAP 1.2."},{"content":"Basic Profile 1.1 requires that the <ph id=\"ph1\">`mustUnderstand`</ph> value be 0 or 1 for SOAP 1.1 messages.","pos":[4830,4921],"source":" Basic Profile 1.1 requires that the `mustUnderstand` value be 0 or 1 for SOAP 1.1 messages."},{"content":"SOAP 1.2 allows 0, 1, <ph id=\"ph1\">`false`</ph>, and <ph id=\"ph2\">`true`</ph> as values, but recommends emitting a canonical representation of <ph id=\"ph3\">`xs:boolean`</ph> values (<ph id=\"ph4\">`false`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph5\">`true`</ph>).","pos":[4922,5067],"source":" SOAP 1.2 allows 0, 1, `false`, and `true` as values, but recommends emitting a canonical representation of `xs:boolean` values (`false`, `true`)."},{"content":"B1112: WCF emits <ph id=\"ph1\">`mustUnderstand`</ph> values 0 and 1 for both SOAP 1.1 and SOAP 1.2 versions of the SOAP envelope.","pos":[5071,5181],"source":"B1112: WCF emits `mustUnderstand` values 0 and 1 for both SOAP 1.1 and SOAP 1.2 versions of the SOAP envelope."},{"content":"WCF accepts the entire value space of <ph id=\"ph1\">`xs:boolean`</ph> for the <ph id=\"ph2\">`mustUnderstand`</ph> header (0, 1, <ph id=\"ph3\">`false`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph4\">`true`</ph>)","pos":[5182,5288],"source":" WCF accepts the entire value space of `xs:boolean` for the `mustUnderstand` header (0, 1, `false`, `true`)"},{"pos":[5295,5306],"content":"SOAP Faults","linkify":"SOAP Faults","nodes":[{"content":"SOAP Faults","pos":[0,11]}]},{"content":"The following is a list of WCF-specific SOAP fault implementations.","pos":[5307,5374]},{"pos":[5378,5486],"content":"B2121: WCF returns the following SOAP 1.1 Fault Codes: <ph id=\"ph1\">`s11:mustUnderstand`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph2\">`s11:Client`</ph>, and <ph id=\"ph3\">`s11:Server`</ph>.","source":"B2121: WCF returns the following SOAP 1.1 Fault Codes: `s11:mustUnderstand`, `s11:Client`, and `s11:Server`."},{"pos":[5490,5600],"content":"B2122: WCF returns the following SOAP 1.2 Fault Codes: <ph id=\"ph1\">`s12:MustUnderstand`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph2\">`s12:Sender`</ph>, and <ph id=\"ph3\">`s12:Receiver`</ph>.","source":"B2122: WCF returns the following SOAP 1.2 Fault Codes: `s12:MustUnderstand`, `s12:Sender`, and `s12:Receiver`."},{"pos":[5606,5618],"content":"HTTP Binding","linkify":"HTTP Binding","nodes":[{"content":"HTTP Binding","pos":[0,12]}]},{"pos":[562