2: The `application/soap+xml` action parameter, when present on a SOAP 1.2 message, must match `wsa:Action` when WS-Addressing 2004/08 or WS-Addressing 1.0 are used."},{"pos":[6703,6841],"content":"When WS-Addressing is disabled and an incoming request does not contain an action parameter, message <ph id=\"ph1\">`Action`</ph> is considered not specified.","source":"When WS-Addressing is disabled and an incoming request does not contain an action parameter, message `Action` is considered not specified."},{"pos":[6846,6859],"content":"WS-Addressing","linkify":"WS-Addressing","nodes":[{"content":"WS-Addressing","pos":[0,13]}]},{"content":"WCF implements 3 versions of WS-Addressing:","pos":[6860,6903]},{"content":"WS-Addressing 2004/08","pos":[6907,6928]},{"content":"W3C Web Services Addressing 1.0 Core  (ADDR10-CORE) and SOAP Binding (ADDR10-SOAP)","pos":[6932,7014]},{"content":"WS-Addressing 1.0 - Metadata","pos":[7018,7046]},{"pos":[7052,7071],"content":"Endpoint References","linkify":"Endpoint References","nodes":[{"content":"Endpoint References","pos":[0,19]}]},{"content":"All versions of WS-Addressing that WCF implements use endpoint references to describe endpoints.","pos":[7072,7168]},{"pos":[7175,7221],"content":"Endpoint References and WS-Addressing Versions","linkify":"Endpoint References and WS-Addressing Versions","nodes":[{"content":"Endpoint References and WS-Addressing Versions","pos":[0,46]}]},{"content":"WCF implements a number of the infrastructure protocols that use WS-Addressing and in particular the <ph id=\"ph1\">`EndpointReference`</ph> element and <ph id=\"ph2\">`W3C.WsAddressing.EndpointReferenceType`</ph> class (for example, WS-ReliableMessaging, WS-SecureConversation, and WS-Trust).","pos":[7222,7475],"source":"WCF implements a number of the infrastructure protocols that use WS-Addressing and in particular the `EndpointReference` element and `W3C.WsAddressing.EndpointReferenceType` class (for example, WS-ReliableMessaging, WS-SecureConversation, and WS-Trust)."},{"content":"WCF supports the use of either version of WS-Addressing with other infrastructure protocols.","pos":[7476,7568]},{"content":"WCF endpoints support one version of WS-Addressing per endpoint.","pos":[7569,7633]},{"pos":[7635,7820],"content":"For R3111, the namespace for the <ph id=\"ph1\">`EndpointReference`</ph> element or type used in messages exchanged with a WCF endpoint must match the version of WS-Addressing implemented by this endpoint.","source":"For R3111, the namespace for the `EndpointReference` element or type used in messages exchanged with a WCF endpoint must match the version of WS-Addressing implemented by this endpoint."},{"pos":[7822,8061],"content":"For example, if a WCF endpoint implements WS-ReliableMessaging, the <ph id=\"ph1\">`AcksTo`</ph> header returned by such an endpoint inside <ph id=\"ph2\">`CreateSequenceResponse`</ph> uses the WS-Addressing version that the <ph id=\"ph3\">`EncodingBinding`</ph> element specifies for this endpoint.","source":"For example, if a WCF endpoint implements WS-ReliableMessaging, the `AcksTo` header returned by such an endpoint inside `CreateSequenceResponse` uses the WS-Addressing version that the `EncodingBinding` element specifies for this endpoint."},{"pos":[8068,8100],"content":"Endpoint References and Metadata","linkify":"Endpoint References and Metadata","nodes":[{"content":"Endpoint References and Metadata","pos":[0,32]}]},{"content":"A number of scenarios require communicating metadata or a reference to metadata for a given endpoint.","pos":[8101,8202]},{"content":"B3121: WCF employs mechanisms described in the WS-MetadataExchange (MEX) specification Section 6 to include metadata for endpoint references by value or by reference.","pos":[8204,8370]},{"content":"Consider a scenario where a WCF service requires authentication using a Security Assertions Markup Language (SAML) token issued by the token issuer at <ph id=\"ph1\">`http://sts.fabrikam123.com`</ph>.","pos":[8372,8552],"source":"Consider a scenario where a WCF service requires authentication using a Security Assertions Markup Language (SAML) token issued by the token issuer at `http://sts.fabrikam123.com`."},{"content":"The WCF endpoint describes this authentication requirement by using <ph id=\"ph1\">`sp:IssuedToken`</ph> assertion with a nested <ph id=\"ph2\">`sp:Issuer`</ph> assertion pointing to the token issuer.","pos":[8553,8713],"source":" The WCF endpoint describes this authentication requirement by using `sp:IssuedToken` assertion with a nested `sp:Issuer` assertion pointing to the token issuer."},{"content":"Client applications that access the <ph id=\"ph1\">`sp:Issuer`</ph> assertion need to know how to communicate with the token issuer endpoint.","pos":[8714,8835],"source":" Client applications that access the `sp:Issuer` assertion need to know how to communicate with the token issuer endpoint."},{"content":"The client needs to know metadata about the token issuer.","pos":[8836,8893]},{"content":"Using the endpoint reference metadata extensions defined in MEX, WCF provides a reference to the token issuer metadata.","pos":[8894,9013]},{"pos":[9487,9513],"content":"Message Addressing Headers","linkify":"Message Addressing Headers","nodes":[{"content":"Message Addressing Headers","pos":[0,26]}]},{"pos":[9520,9535],"content":"Message Headers","linkify":"Message Headers","nodes":[{"content":"Message Headers","pos":[0,15]}]},{"pos":[9536,9719],"content":"For both WS-Addressing versions, WCF uses the following message headers as prescribed by the specifications <ph id=\"ph1\">`wsa:To`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph2\">`wsa:ReplyTo`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph3\">`wsa:Action`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph4\">`wsa:MessageID`</ph>,and <ph id=\"ph5\">`wsa:RelatesTo`</ph>.","source":"For both WS-Addressing versions, WCF uses the following message headers as prescribed by the specifications `wsa:To`, `wsa:ReplyTo`, `wsa:Action`, `wsa:MessageID`,and `wsa:RelatesTo`."},{"pos":[9721,9868],"content":"B3211: For all WS-Addressing versions, WCF honors, but does not produce out of the box, WS-Addressing message headers <ph id=\"ph1\">`wsa:FaultTo`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">`wsa:From`</ph>.","source":"B3211: For all WS-Addressing versions, WCF honors, but does not produce out of the box, WS-Addressing message headers `wsa:FaultTo` and `wsa:From`."},{"content":"Applications that interact with WCF applications can add these message headers and WCF will process them accordingly.","pos":[9870,9987]},{"pos":[9994,10029],"content":"Reference Parameters and Properties","linkify":"Reference Parameters and Properties","nodes":[{"content":"Reference Parameters and Properties","pos":[0,35]}]},{"content":"WCF implements processing of endpoint reference parameters and reference properties in accordance with respective specifications.","pos":[10031,10160]},{"content":"B3221: When configured to use WS-Addressing 2004/08, WCF endpoints do not differentiate between processing Reference Properties and Reference Parameters.","pos":[10162,10315]},{"pos":[10321,10346],"content":"Message Exchange Patterns","linkify":"Message Exchange Patterns","nodes":[{"content":"Message Exchange Patterns","pos":[0,25]}]},{"content":"The sequence of messages involved in the Web service operation invocation is referred to as the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>message exchange pattern<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.","pos":[10347,10470],"source":"The sequence of messages involved in the Web service operation invocation is referred to as the *message exchange pattern*."},{"content":"WCF supports one-way, request-reply, and duplex message exchange patterns.","pos":[10471,10545]},{"content":"This section clarifies WS-Addressing requirements on message processing depending on the message exchange pattern being used.","pos":[10546,10671]},{"content":"Throughout this section, the requester sends the first message and the responder receives the first message.","pos":[10673,10781]},{"pos":[10788,10803],"content":"One-Way Message","linkify":"One-