s required by SOAP 1.2."},{"content":"Parameters <ph id=\"ph1\">`charset`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">`action`</ph> are included.","pos":[22734,22781],"source":" Parameters `charset` and `action` are included."},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">`action`</ph> parameter of the Content-Type header matches the value of the <ph id=\"ph2\">`wsa10:Action`</ph> message header.","pos":[22782,22887],"source":" The `action` parameter of the Content-Type header matches the value of the `wsa10:Action` message header."},{"content":"The receiver responds with an empty HTTP response and status 202.","pos":[23533,23598]},{"content":"An example of the HTTP response:","pos":[23599,23631]},{"pos":[23854,23902],"content":"SOAP Message Transmission Optimization Mechanism","linkify":"SOAP Message Transmission Optimization Mechanism","nodes":[{"content":"SOAP Message Transmission Optimization Mechanism","pos":[0,48]}]},{"content":"This section describes the WCF implementation details for the HTTP SOAP MTOM.","pos":[23903,23980]},{"content":"MTOM technology is SOAP message encoding mechanism of the same class as traditional text/XML encoding or WCF Binary encoding.","pos":[23981,24106]},{"content":"MTOM includes the following:","pos":[24107,24135]},{"content":"An XML encoding and packaging mechanism described by [XOP] that optimizes XML information items containing base64-encoded binary data into separate binary parts.","pos":[24139,24300]},{"content":"A MIME encapsulation of the XOP package that serializes the XML Infoset and each binary part of the XOP package into a separate MIME part.","pos":[24304,24442]},{"content":"A MIME XOP encoding applied to SOAP 1.x Envelope.","pos":[24446,24495]},{"content":"An HTTP transport binding.","pos":[24499,24525]},{"content":"It is possible to use MTOM with non-HTTP transports with WCF.","pos":[24527,24588]},{"content":"However, in this topic we will focus on HTTP.","pos":[24589,24634]},{"content":"The MTOM format leverages a large set of specifications covering MTOM itself, XOP, and MIME.","pos":[24636,24728]},{"content":"Modularity of this specification set makes it somewhat difficult to reconstruct exact requirements on the format and processing semantics.","pos":[24729,24867]},{"content":"This section describes the format and processing requirements for MTOM HTTP binding.","pos":[24868,24952]},{"pos":[24958,24979],"content":"MTOM Message Encoding","linkify":"MTOM Message Encoding","nodes":[{"content":"MTOM Message Encoding","pos":[0,21]}]},{"pos":[24986,25010],"content":"Generating MTOM messages","linkify":"Generating MTOM messages","nodes":[{"content":"Generating MTOM messages","pos":[0,24]}]},{"content":"The [XOP] section 3.1 describes the process of encoding XML with element information items that contain base64 values into an abstractly defined XOP package.","pos":[25011,25168]},{"content":"The following sequence of steps describes the MTOM-specific encoding process:","pos":[25170,25247]},{"pos":[25252,25436],"content":"Ensure that the SOAP Envelope to be encoded contains no element information item with a <ph id=\"ph1\">`[namespace name]`</ph> of <ph id=\"ph2\">`http://www.w3.org/2004/08/xop/include`</ph> and a <ph id=\"ph3\">`[local name]`</ph> of <ph id=\"ph4\">`Include`</ph>.","source":"Ensure that the SOAP Envelope to be encoded contains no element information item with a `[namespace name]` of `http://www.w3.org/2004/08/xop/include` and a `[local name]` of `Include`."},{"content":"Create an empty MIME package.","pos":[25441,25470]},{"content":"Identify within the Original XML Infoset the element information items to be optimized.","pos":[25475,25562]},{"content":"For the items to be optimized, the characters that make up the <ph id=\"ph1\">`[children]`</ph> of the element information item must be in the canonical form of <ph id=\"ph2\">`xs:base64Binary`</ph> (see XSD-2, 3.2.16 base64Binary) and must not contain any white-space characters preceding, inline with, or following the non-white-space content.","pos":[25563,25868],"source":" For the items to be optimized, the characters that make up the `[children]` of the element information item must be in the canonical form of `xs:base64Binary` (see XSD-2, 3.2.16 base64Binary) and must not contain any white-space characters preceding, inline with, or following the non-white-space content."},{"pos":[25873,26111],"content":"Create an XOP SOAP Envelope that is a copy of the Original SOAP Envelope, but with the children of each element information item identified in the previous step replaced by an <ph id=\"ph1\">`xop:Include`</ph> element information item constructed as follows:","source":"Create an XOP SOAP Envelope that is a copy of the Original SOAP Envelope, but with the children of each element information item identified in the previous step replaced by an `xop:Include` element information item constructed as follows:"},{"content":"Transform the replaced characters into binary data by processing them as base64-encoded data.","pos":[26120,26213]},{"content":"Generate a unique Content-ID header value that satisfies requirements R3133 and R3134.","pos":[26222,26308]},{"content":"Generate a Content-Transfer-Encoding MIME header with the value binary.","pos":[26317,26388]},{"pos":[26397,26664],"content":"If the element information item being optimized (the [parent] of the newly inserted <ph id=\"ph1\">`xop:Include`</ph> element information item) has an <ph id=\"ph2\">`xmime:contentType`</ph> attribute information item, generate a Content-Type MIME header with the value of the <ph id=\"ph3\">`xmime:contentType`</ph> attribute.","source":"If the element information item being optimized (the [parent] of the newly inserted `xop:Include` element information item) has an `xmime:contentType` attribute information item, generate a Content-Type MIME header with the value of the `xmime:contentType` attribute."},{"content":"Generate a new binary MIME part with content formed by binary data decoded from the replaced characters processed as base64, Content-ID header from 4b, Content- Transfer-Encoding header from 4c, Content-Type header if generated in step 4d.","pos":[26673,26912]},{"content":"Add an <ph id=\"ph1\">`href`</ph> attribute to the <ph id=\"ph2\">`xop:Include`</ph> element with the value cid: uri derived from Content-ID header value generated in step 4b.","pos":[26921,27056],"source":"Add an `href` attribute to the `xop:Include` element with the value cid: uri derived from Content-ID header value generated in step 4b."},{"content":"Remove the enclosing \"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>\" and \"&gt;\" characters, URL-escape the remaining string, and add the prefix <ph id=\"ph2\">`cid:`</ph>.","pos":[27057,27162],"source":" Remove the enclosing \"\\<\" and \">\" characters, URL-escape the remaining string, and add the prefix `cid:`."},{"content":"The following minimum character set is required to be escaped by RFC1738 and RFC2396.","pos":[27163,27248]},{"content":"Other characters can be escaped.","pos":[27249,27281]},{"content":"Create a root MIME part with the XOP SOAP Envelope from step 4.","pos":[27441,27504]},{"content":"Write the HTTP headers, including the HTTP Content-Type header.","pos":[27509,27572]},{"content":"Write the MIME package.","pos":[27577,27600]},{"pos":[27607,27631],"content":"Processing MTOM messages","linkify":"Processing MTOM messages","nodes":[{"content":"Processing MTOM messages","pos":[0,24]}]},{"content":"Processing of an MTOM message is the exact reverse of the process described in the preceding \"Generating MTOM messages\" section:","pos":[27632,27760]},{"pos":[27765,27834],"content":"Ensure the root MIME part has the Content-Type <ph id=\"ph1\">`application/xop+xml`</ph>.","source":"Ensure the root MIME part has the Content-Type `application/xop+xml`."},{"content":"Construct a SOAP Envelope by parsing the root MIME part of the package as an XML document.","pos":[27839,27929]},{"content":"Character encoding is determined by the <ph id=\"ph1\">`charset`</ph> parameter of the Content-Type of the root MIME part.","pos":[27930,28032],"source":" Character encoding is determined by the `charset` parameter of the Content-Type of the root MIME part."},{"pos":[28037,28205],"content":"For each element information item in the constructed SOAP Envelope, which has, as the sole member of its [children] property, an <ph id=\"ph1\">`xop:Include`</ph> element information item:","source":"For each element information item in the constructed SOAP Envelope, which has, as the sole member of its [children] property, an `xop:Include` element information item:"},{"content":"Remove the <ph id=\"ph1\">`cid:`</ph> prefix and unescape all URI-escape sequences (RFC 2396) in the value of the <ph id=\"ph2\">`@href`</ph> attribute of the <ph id=\"ph3\">`xop:Include`</ph> element.","pos":[28214,28355],"source":"Remove the `cid:` prefix and unescape all URI-escape sequences (RFC 2396) in the value of the `@href` attribute of the `xop:Include` element."},{"content":"Enclose the result string in \"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>\", \"&gt;\".","pos":[28356,28395],"source":" Enclose the result string in \"\\<\", \">\"."},{"content":"Locate the MIME part with the Content-ID header value that matches the string derived in step 3a.","pos":[28404,28501]},{"pos":[28510,28902],"content":"Replace the <ph id=\"ph1\">`xop:Include`</ph> element information item that appears in the <ph id=\"ph2\">`children`</ph> property of each item with the character information items that represent the canonical base64 encoding (see XSD-2, 3.2.16 base64Binary) of the entity body of the MIME part identified in step 3b (effectively replace the <ph id=\"ph3\">`xop:Include`</ph> element information item with the data reconstructed from the package part).","source":"Replace the `xop:Include` element information item that appears in the `children` property of each item with the character information items that represent the canonical base64 encoding (see XSD-2, 3.2.16 base64Binary) of the entity body of the MIME part identified in step 3b (effectively replace the `xop:Include` element information item with the data reconstructed from the package part)."},{"pos":[28909,28933],"content":"HTTP Content-Type Header","linkify":"HTTP Content-Type Header","nodes":[{"content":"HTTP Content-Type Header","pos":[0,24]}]},{"content":"The following is a list of WCF clarifications for the format of the HTTP Content-Type header of a SOAP 1.x MTOM-encoded message derived from requirements stated in the MTOM specification itself and are derived from MTOM and RFC 2387.","pos":[28934,29167]},{"content":"R4131: An HTTP Content-Type header must have the value of multipart/related (case-insensitive) and its parameters.","pos":[29171,29285]},{"content":"Parameter names are case-insensitive.","pos":[29286,29323]},{"content":"Parameter order is not significant.","pos":[29324,29359]},{"content":"The full Backus-Naur Form (BNF) of the Content-Type header for MIME messages is listed in RFC 2045, section 5.1.","pos":[29363,29475]},{"pos":[29479,29613],"content":"R4132: An HTTP Content-Type header must have a type parameter with the value <ph id=\"ph1\">`application/xop+xml`</ph> enclosed in double quotation marks.","source":"R4132: An HTTP Content-Type header must have a type parameter with the value `application/xop+xml` enclosed in double quotation marks."},{"content":"While the requirement to use double quotation marks is not explicit in RFC 2387, the text observes that all of the multipart/related media type parameters most likely contain reserved characters like \"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\@</ph>\" or \"/\" and therefore need double quotation marks.","pos":[29615,29869],"source":"While the requirement to use double quotation marks is not explicit in RFC 2387, the text observes that all of the multipart/related media type parameters most likely contain reserved characters like \"\\@\" or \"/\" and therefore need double quotation marks."},{"content":"R4133: An HTTP Content-Type header should have a start parameter with the value of the Content-ID header of the MIME part that contains the SOAP 1.x Envelope, enclosed in double quotation marks.","pos":[29873,30067]},{"content":"If the start parameter is omitted, the first MIME part must contain the SOAP 1.x Envelope.","pos":[30068,30158]},{"content":"R4134: An HTTP Content-Type header for a SOAP 1.1 MTOM encoded message must include the start-info parameter with the value of text/xml, enclosed in double quotation marks.","pos":[30162,30334]},{"pos":[30338,30524],"content":"R4135: An HTTP Content-Type header for a SOAP 1.2 MTOM-encoded message must include the start-info parameter with the value of <ph id=\"ph1\">`application/soap+xml`</ph>, enclosed in double quotation marks.","source":"R4135: An HTTP Content-Type header for a SOAP 1.2 MTOM-encoded message must include the start-info parameter with the value of `application/soap+xml`, enclosed in double quotation marks."},{"content":"R4136: HTTP Content-Type header for a SOAP 1.x MTOM-encoded message must have the boundary parameter with the value (enclosed in double quotation marks) that matches the MIME boundary BNF defined in RFC 2046, section 5.1.1","pos":[30528,30750]},{"content":"Examples:","pos":[30988,30997]},{"content":"CORRECT","pos":[31004,31011]},{"content":"CORRECT","pos":[31208,31215]},{"content":"INCORRECT","pos":[31383,31392]},{"pos":[31588,31605],"content":"Infoset MIME Part","linkify":"Infoset MIME Part","nodes":[{"content":"Infoset MIME Part","pos":[0,17]}]},{"pos":[31606,31722],"content":"The SOAP 1.x Envelope is encapsulated as a root part of the XOP MIME package and is often called the <ph id=\"ph1\">`infoset`</ph> part.","source":"The SOAP 1.x Envelope is encapsulated as a root part of the XOP MIME package and is often called the `infoset` part."},{"pos":[31726,31884],"content":"R4141: The SOAP 1.x Envelope must be encapsulated as a root part of the XOP MIME package, called the <ph id=\"ph1\">`infoset`</ph> part and referenced from