;</ph>\" and \"&gt;\" to be an email address and used <ph id=\"ph2\">`absoluteURI`</ph> enclosed in \"<ph id=\"ph3\">\\&lt;</ph>\" , \"&gt;\" in addition to the email address.","pos":[32642,32841],"source":"A number of MIME implementations relaxed requirements for the value enclosed within \"\\<\" and \">\" to be an email address and used `absoluteURI` enclosed in \"\\<\" , \">\" in addition to the email address."},{"content":"This version of WCF uses values of the Content-ID MIME header of the form:","pos":[32842,32916]},{"pos":[32963,33067],"content":"R4144: MTOM processors should accept Content-ID header values that match the following relaxed <ph id=\"ph1\">`msg-id`</ph>.","source":"R4144: MTOM processors should accept Content-ID header values that match the following relaxed `msg-id`."},{"content":"MIME (RFC 2045) provides the Content-Transfer-Encoding header to communicate encoding of the content of the MIME part.","pos":[33192,33310]},{"content":"The default defined for Content-Transfer-Encoding is 7-bit, which is not suitable for most SOAP messages, so the Content-Transfer-Encoding header is needed for greater interoperability:","pos":[33311,33496]},{"content":"R4145: The SOAP Infoset part must contain the Content-Transfer-Encoding header.","pos":[33500,33579]},{"content":"R4146: If the SOAP Envelope character encoding is UTF-8, the value of the Content-Transfer-Encoding header must be 8-bit.","pos":[33583,33704]},{"content":"R4147: If the SOAP Envelope character encoding is UTF-16, the value of the Content-Transfer-Encoding header must be binary.","pos":[33708,33831]},{"content":"According to [XOP] section 5,","pos":[33835,33864]},{"content":"R4148: SOAP1.1 Infoset part must contain Content-Type header with media type application/xop+xml and parameters type=\"text/xml\" and charset","pos":[33868,34007]},{"pos":[34115,34282],"content":"R4149: The SOAP 1.2 Infoset part must contain the Content-Type header with media type <ph id=\"ph1\">`application/xop+xml`</ph> and parameters type=\"<ph id=\"ph2\">`application/soap+xml`</ph>\" and <ph id=\"ph3\">`charset`</ph>.","source":"R4149: The SOAP 1.2 Infoset part must contain the Content-Type header with media type `application/xop+xml` and parameters type=\"`application/soap+xml`\" and `charset`."},{"pos":[34405,34614],"content":"While XOP defines the <ph id=\"ph1\">`charset`</ph> parameter for <ph id=\"ph2\">`application/xop+xml`</ph> to be optional, it is needed for interoperability similar to the BP 1.1 requirement on the <ph id=\"ph3\">`charset`</ph> parameter for the <ph id=\"ph4\">`text/xml`</ph> media type.","source":"While XOP defines the `charset` parameter for `application/xop+xml` to be optional, it is needed for interoperability similar to the BP 1.1 requirement on the `charset` parameter for the `text/xml` media type."},{"pos":[34618,34734],"content":"R41410: The <ph id=\"ph1\">`type`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">`charset`</ph> parameters must be present on the Content-Type header of the SOAP 1.x Infoset part.","source":"R41410: The `type` and `charset` parameters must be present on the Content-Type header of the SOAP 1.x Infoset part."},{"pos":[34741,34770],"content":"WCF Endpoint Support for MTOM","linkify":"WCF Endpoint Support for MTOM","nodes":[{"content":"WCF Endpoint Support for MTOM","pos":[0,29]}]},{"content":"The purpose of MTOM is to encode a SOAP message to optimize base64-encoded data.","pos":[34771,34851]},{"content":"The following is a list of constraints:","pos":[34852,34891]},{"content":"R4151: Any element information item that contains base64-encoded data may be optimized.","pos":[34895,34982]},{"content":"B4152: WCF optimizes element information items that contain base64-encoded data and exceed 1024 bytes in length.","pos":[34986,35098]},{"content":"A WCF endpoint configured to use MTOM will always send MTOM-encoded messages.","pos":[35100,35177]},{"content":"Even if no parts meet the required criteria, the message is still MTOM-encoded (serialized as a MIME package with a single MIME part containing the SOAP envelope).","pos":[35178,35341]},{"pos":[35347,35375],"content":"WS-Policy Assertion for MTOM","linkify":"WS-Policy Assertion for MTOM","nodes":[{"content":"WS-Policy Assertion for MTOM","pos":[0,28]}]},{"content":"WCF uses the following policy assertion to indicate MTOM usage by endpoint:","pos":[35376,35451]},{"content":"R4211: The preceding policy assertion has an Endpoint Policy Subject and specifies that all messages sent to and received from the endpoint must be optimized using MTOM.","pos":[35508,35677]},{"pos":[35681,35835],"content":"B4212: When configured to use MTOM optimization, an WCF endpoint adds an MTOM Policy assertion to the policy attached to the corresponding <ph id=\"ph1\">`wsdl:binding`</ph>.","source":"B4212: When configured to use MTOM optimization, an WCF endpoint adds an MTOM Policy assertion to the policy attached to the corresponding `wsdl:binding`."},{"pos":[35841,35869],"content":"Composition with WS-Security","linkify":"Composition with WS-Security","nodes":[{"content":"Composition with WS-Security","pos":[0,28]}]},{"content":"MTOM is an encoding mechanism that is similar to <ph id=\"ph1\">`text/xml`</ph> and WCF Binary XML.","pos":[35870,35949],"source":"MTOM is an encoding mechanism that is similar to `text/xml` and WCF Binary XML."},{"content":"MTOM offers natural composition with WS-Security and other WS-* protocols: a message secured using WS-Security can be optimized using MTOM.","pos":[35950,36089]},{"pos":[36095,36103],"content":"Examples","linkify":"Examples","nodes":[{"content":"Examples","pos":[0,8]}]},{"pos":[36110,36149],"content":"WCF SOAP 1.1 Message Encoded Using MTOM","linkify":"WCF SOAP 1.1 Message Encoded Using MTOM","nodes":[{"content":"WCF SOAP 1.1 Message Encoded Using MTOM","pos":[0,39]}]},{"pos":[37311,37357],"content":"WCF Secure SOAP 1.2 Message Encoded Using MTOM","linkify":"WCF Secure SOAP 1.2 Message Encoded Using MTOM","nodes":[{"content":"WCF Secure SOAP 1.2 Message Encoded Using MTOM","pos":[0,46]}]},{"content":"In this example, a message is encoded using MTOM and SOAP 1.2 that is protected using WS-Security.","pos":[37358,37456]},{"content":"The binary parts identified for encoding are the contents of the <ph id=\"ph1\">`BinarySecurityToken`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph2\">`CipherValue`</ph> of the <ph id=\"ph3\">`EncryptedData`</ph> corresponding to the encrypted signature and encrypted body.","pos":[37457,37642],"source":" The binary parts identified for encoding are the contents of the `BinarySecurityToken`, `CipherValue` of the `EncryptedData` corresponding to the encrypted signature and encrypted body."},{"content":"Note that the <ph id=\"ph1\">`CipherValue`</ph> of the <ph id=\"ph2\">`EncryptedKey`</ph> was not identified for optimization by WCF, because its length is less then 1024 bytes.","pos":[37643,37780],"source":" Note that the `CipherValue` of the `EncryptedKey` was not identified for optimization by WCF, because its length is less then 1024 bytes."}]}